\n71: ### Task 4: Implement error types and conversion\n72: - [ ] Define error types in `errors.go`\n73:   - [ ] `ErrorResponse struct` - Standardized error response\n74:     - [ ] `Code string` - Error code\n75:     - [ ] `Message string` - Error message\n76:     - [ ] `Details map[string]interface{}` - Additional error details\n77:   - [ ] `ErrorCode type` - Type for error codes\n78: - [ ] Define error codes\n79:   - [ ] `ErrCodeRuntimeNotFound = \"RuntimeNotFound\"`\n80:   - [ ] `ErrCodeInterpreterNotFound = \"InterpreterNotFound\"`\n81:   - [ ] `ErrCodeInvalidRequest = \"InvalidRequest\"`\n82:   - [ ] `ErrCodeUnauthorized = \"Unauthorized\"`\n83:   - [ ] `ErrCodeForbidden = \"Forbidden\"`\n84:   - [ ] `ErrCodeInternalError = \"InternalError\"`\n85:   - [ ] `ErrCodeConflict = \"Conflict\"`\n86: - [ ] Implement `NewErrorResponse(code, message string) *ErrorResponse`\n87: - [ ] Implement `NewErrorResponseWithDetails(code, message string, details map[string]interface{}) *ErrorResponse`\n88: - [ ] Implement `WriteJSONError(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, errResp *ErrorResponse)`\n89: - [ ] Implement `K8sErrorToHTTP(err error) (int, *ErrorResponse)`\n90:   - [ ] Handle `IsNotFound()` -> 404 RuntimeNotFound/InterpreterNotFound\n91:   - [ ] Handle `IsConflict()` -> 409 Conflict\n92:   - [ ] Handle `IsUnauthorized()` -> 401 Unauthorized\n93:   - [ ] Handle `IsForbidden()` -> 403 Forbidden\n94:   - [ ] Handle generic errors -> 500 InternalError\n95: - [ ] Create `errors_test.go` with unit tests\n96:   - [ ] Test error response creation\n97:   - [ ] Test K8s error to HTTP conversion for various error types\n98: \n99: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestError` to verify error handling tests pass\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### Task 5: Implement response formatting\n104: - [ ] Define response structures in `response.go`\n105:   - [ ] `SuccessResponse struct` - Standard success response\n106:     - [ ] `Data interface{}` - Response data\n107:     - [ ] `Metadata map[string]interface{}` - Response metadata\n108:   - [ ] `ListResponse struct` - List response with pagination\n109:     - [ ] `Items []interface{}` - List items\n110:     - [ ] `Continue string` - Continue token for pagination\n111:     - [ ] `RemainingItemCount int64` - Remaining item count\n112: - [ ] Implement `WriteJSONResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, statusCode int, data interface{}) error`\n113: - [ ] Implement `WriteJSONSuccess(w http.ResponseWriter, data interface{}) error`\n114: - [ ] Implement `WriteJSONList(w http.ResponseWriter, items []interface{}, continueToken string, remainingCount int64) error`\n115: - [ ] Add JSON content-type header setting\n116: - [ ] Handle JSON marshaling errors\n117: - [ ] Create `response_test.go` with unit tests\n118:   - [ ] Test success response writing\n119:   - [ ] Test list response writing\n120:   - [ ] Test JSON error handling\n121: \n122: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestResponse` to verify response formatting tests pass\n123: \n124: ---\n125: \n126: ### Task 6: Implement request validation\n127: - [ ] Define validation utilities in `validation.go`\n128: - [ ] Implement `ValidateRequestBody(obj interface{}) error`\n129:   - [ ] Decode JSON from request body\n130:   - [ ] Validate JSON schema if schema provided\n131:   - [ ] Validate required fields\n132:   - [ ] Return validation errors with details\n133: - [ ] Implement `ValidateJSONBody(r *http.Request, obj interface{}) error`\n134:   - [ ] Read request body\n135:   - [ ] Parse JSON into target struct\n136:   - [ ] Validate struct tags (json, required, etc.)\n137: - [ ] Implement `ValidateName(name string) error`\n138:   - [ ] Check name is not empty\n139:   - [ ] Check name meets DNS label requirements (lowercase, alphanumeric, hyphens)\n140:   - [ ] Check name length (max 253 characters)\n141: - [ ] Create `validation_test.go` with unit tests\n142:   - [ ] Test valid request body validation\n143:   - [ ] Test in