ware panic handling\n182:   - [ ] Test CORS middleware header setting\n183:   - [ ] Test request ID middleware ID generation\n184: \n185: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestMiddleware` to verify middleware tests pass\n186: \n187: ---\n188: \n189: ### Task 8: Implement Prometheus metrics\n190: - [ ] Add Prometheus client dependency\n191:   - [ ] Run `go get github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus`\n192:   - [ ] Run `go get github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus/promhttp`\n193:   - [ ] Run `go mod tidy`\n194: - [ ] Define Metrics struct in `metrics.go`\n195:   - [ ] `HTTPRequestsTotal *prometheus.CounterVec` - Total HTTP requests\n196:   - [ ] `HTTPRequestDuration *prometheus.HistogramVec` - Request duration\n197:   - [ ] `HTTPRequestsInFlight *prometheus.GaugeVec` - Requests in flight\n198: - [ ] Implement `NewMetrics(reg prometheus.Registerer) *Metrics`\n199:   - [ ] Register HTTP request counter (labels: method, endpoint, status)\n200:   - [ ] Register request duration histogram (labels: method, endpoint)\n201:   - [ ] Register requests in flight gauge (labels: method, endpoint)\n202: - [ ] Implement `MetricsMiddleware(metrics *Metrics) Middleware`\n203:   - [ ] Increment request counter at start\n204:   - [ ] Record request duration at end\n205:   - [ ] Update requests in flight gauge\n206: - [ ] Implement `MetricsHandler() http.Handler` for /metrics endpoint\n207:   - [ ] Use promhttp.Handler() to expose metrics\n208: - [ ] Create `metrics_test.go` with unit tests\n209:   - [ ] Test metrics counter increment\n210:   - [ ] Test metrics histogram recording\n211:   - [ ] Test metrics gauge update\n212: \n213: **Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestMetrics` to verify metrics tests pass\n214: \n215: ---\n216: \n217: ### Task 9: Implement Server structure and lifecycle\n218: - [ ] Define Server struct in `server.go`\n219:   - [ ] `httpServer *http.Server` - Underlying HTTP server\n220:   - [ ] `router *mu